descriptions.check:
Perform the following to check NIS file ownership:
# ls -la /var/yp/*;
If the file ownership is not root, sys, or bin, this is a finding.

Perform the following to check NIS file premissions.
# ls -la /var/yp/*;
If the file's mode is more permissive than 0755, this is a finding.

descriptions.fix:
Remove all the r-commands access control files.

Procedure:
# find / -name .rhosts -exec rm {} \;
# find / -name .shosts -exec rm {} \;
# find / -name hosts.equiv -exec rm {} \;
# find / -name shosts.equiv -exec rm {} \;

descriptions.check:
Check the mode of scripts in cron job directories.

ls -lL /etc/cron.{d,daily,hourly,monthly,weekly}
If any cron script has a mode more permissive than 0700, this is a finding.

descriptions.fix:
Change the mode of the alias files as needed to function. No higher than 0644.
Procedure:
for sendmail:
# chmod 0644 /etc/aliases /etc/aliases.db

for postfix:
# chmod 0644 <postfix aliases file> <postfix aliases.db file>

Remove the extended permissions from the alias files.
Procedure:
for sendmail:
# setfacl --remove-all /etc/aliases /etc/aliases.db

for postfix:
# setfacl --remove-all <postfix aliases file> <postfix aliases.db file>
